Just out of curiosity, is anyone in this group going to GECCO that I
might not know about?  I know several people are going but it would be
interesting to know anyone else.

For those who don't know, GECCO is the Genetic and Evolutionary
Computation Conference, which is the major conference in the
Evolutionary Computation field.  This year it's in Seattle June 26-30.
I definitely recommend for anyone who hasn't gone.  It's my favorite
conference among those I've attended.

ken
